<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="183" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                    <head>No. 183.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-03-19"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 19, 1888</date>.
                            (Received May 5.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 591.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the Tsung-li
                        Yamên has agreed that arrangements will be made to relieve the foreigners
                        from the present unsatisfactory system of “drawbacks” on the Yangtze. The
                        exact changes to be made have not been determined.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles
                            Denby.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>